Title: Introduction to Topology and Differential Geometry
Q: What is the relation between Betti numbers and Euler characteristic?
A: The Euler characteristic of a topological space is equal to the alternating sum of its Betti numbers, expressed mathematically as chi = b_0 - b_1 + b_2 - b_3 + ...
